<heading> UCI Podcast: UCI Health response to pandemic </heading>
<sub_heading> N/A </sub_heading>
<date> April 10, 2020 </date>
<article> The entire UCI community is confronting the coronavirus pandemic with unprecedented actions. UCI Health is on the front lines of the crisis response. In this episode of the UCI Podcast, two key members of the UCI Health staff – Linda Dickey, senior director of quality & patient safety, epidemiology & infection prevention; and Joe Brothman, director of environmental health & safety – discuss the measures UCI Health has undertaken thus far to prepare for a potential surge in COVID-19 cases and ongoing efforts to keep the community safe and healthy.
  </article>
